-- Government to Cut Annual Tax-Privileged Pension Saving Limit to $80,000
-- B y   G o n z a l o   V i n a
-- 2010-10-14T08:55:04Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-14/government-to-cut-annual-tax-privileged-pension-saving-limit-to-80-000.html
U.K. Treasury Minister Mark Hoban
said the coalition government will reduce the tax-privileged
pension saving limit to 50,000 pounds ($80,000) a year from
255,000 pounds, raising about 4 billion pounds a year to help
cut the record budget deficit.  The lifetime allowance will be reduced to 1.5 milliion
pounds from 1.8 million pounds, Hoban said in a statement posted
